criterion_1.information: The valid humanly plausible ranges for blood glucose are [1.2, 110] mmol/L according to Barry (2020) and Manappallil (2017)

criterion_2.information: According to Walsh et. al. (2014), subcutaneous insulin may not have been administered in the last 6 hours prior the period considered (so 12hours before the time of evaluation)

check_1.information: Required fields exist (diabeticStatus, startTime, bloodGlucose, insulinInfusion, insulinBolus, nutritionInfusion, nutritionBolus)

check_2.information: Both IV insulin and nutrition rates cannot be null at the same time

check_4.information: At least 3 blood glucose measurements in the last 6 hours
